description:
Use this function to list the contents of a folder. Input: folder name or path. Standard folder names include: 'Documents', 'Downloads', 'Desktop', 'Pictures', 'Music', 'Videos'. Output: an object describing the result of the operation.

Return value:
{
"role": "tool",
"status": "success" | "error",
"files": [ "array of file names" ],
"error_message": "string | null"
}

Example function call parameter: { "folder": "Documents" }

Example successful response:
{
"role": "tool",
"status": "success",
"files": [ "file1.txt", "file2.docx" ],
"error_message": null
}

Example error response:
{
"role": "tool",
"status": "error",
"files": [],
"error_message": "Folder not found."
}
